The paper discusses the use of BERT and commonsense knowledge for reading comprehension, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). The most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language) which deals with NLP and its applications. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Learning) are also likely as they deal with machine learning and AI. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity) are less likely but still possible as they deal with information retrieval and algorithms, which are relevant to the paper's methodology.
